00:22:26,437 --> 00:22:29,340
I used to frequently say, "I'll possess you" or "I'll curse you",

515
00:22:29,340 --> 00:22:31,442
"but I never ever said "die".

516
00:22:31,442 --> 00:22:32,743
The only one who says something like that,

517
00:22:32,743 --> 00:22:35,045
is the monster that comes on in the Kamen Yaiba show.

518
00:22:37,648 --> 00:22:41,552
I've fallen low to that level.

519
00:22:41,552 --> 00:22:42,653
But that's...

520
00:22:42,653 --> 00:22:45,756
Besides, after her letters stopped coming,

521
00:22:45,756 --> 00:22:47,258
I got to thinking.

522
00:22:47,258 --> 00:22:49,260
What did I do wrong,

523
00:22:49,260 --> 00:22:51,862
or what did she not like about me?

524
00:22:51,862 --> 00:22:54,965
When I started thinking this way, tears started pourings

525
00:22:54,965 --> 00:22:57,334
and I couldn't compose nor write lyrics.

526
00:22:57,334 --> 00:22:59,336
I couldn't write even a phrase.

527
00:22:59,336 --> 00:23:01,338
Phooey, talk about a fallen devil.

528
00:23:03,240 --> 00:23:05,543
Your tears are a bit red?

529
00:23:05,543 --> 00:23:08,546
That's President Urushibara's blood that splattered on him.

530
00:23:08,546 --> 00:23:09,547
Blood?

531
00:23:15,352 --> 00:23:18,556
You couldn't see colors very well using the ruler mirror, right?

532
00:23:18,556 --> 00:23:21,158
So, you put foundation

533
00:23:21,158 --> 00:23:23,961
right over the blood by your eyes without noticing.

534
00:23:23,961 --> 00:23:25,663
You noticed it only after

535
00:23:25,663 --> 00:23:28,766
your manager bought the mirror and gave it to you.

536
00:23:28,766 --> 00:23:31,335
That's why you couldn't use eye drops.

537
00:23:31,335 --> 00:23:33,037
Because if you did, the eye drop

538
00:23:33,037 --> 00:23:35,139
would wet the area around your eyes, resulting in conclusive evidence.

539
00:23:35,139 --> 00:23:37,241
-I see. -I see.

540
00:23:37,241 --> 00:23:39,143
Shall we go then?

541
00:23:41,245 --> 00:23:43,847
But it sure is like a fairy tale.

542
00:23:45,049 --> 00:23:47,451
Well, like they say,

543
00:23:47,451 --> 00:23:49,653
"When a devil sheds tears,

544
00:23:49,653 --> 00:23:52,156
he loses his evil powers".

545
00:25:23,747 --> 00:25:25,449
Now, something very shocking has happened!

546
00:25:25,449 --> 00:25:28,452
Ms. Kazuka Inoue, Yoko Okino and Azusa Yamamoto

547
00:25:28,452 --> 00:25:30,954
-have aligned in a row with nine correct answers! -You can do it!

548
00:25:30,954 --> 00:25:32,956
There is only one more question to go.

549
00:25:32,956 --> 00:25:34,958
If any one of the three answers correctly,

550
00:25:34,958 --> 00:25:36,460
she will be the winner!

551
00:25:36,460 --> 00:25:38,162
This program was shot

552
00:25:38,162 --> 00:25:41,065
when you went to the TV station the other day, right?

553
00:25:41,065 --> 00:25:43,834
Yes, but I didn't get to see Yoko after the incident,

554
00:25:43,834 --> 00:25:46,136
so I don't know how it turned out.

555
00:25:46,136 --> 00:25:47,838
What else can the result be,

556
00:25:47,838 --> 00:25:49,339
but Yoko answering ten questions correctly

557
00:25:49,339 --> 00:25:51,642
and winning first prize?

558
00:25:51,642 --> 00:25:54,144
Ms. Inoue, do you have confidence?

559
00:25:54,144 --> 00:25:56,747
I'll do my best!

560
00:25:56,747 --> 00:25:58,148
Ms. Okino.

561
00:25:58,148 --> 00:25:59,550
My fans out there.

562
00:25:59,550 --> 00:26:00,951
Root for me, okay?

563
00:26:00,951 --> 00:26:03,354
Of course, of course! I'll root for you!

564
00:26:03,354 --> 00:26:05,255
Ms. Yamamoto?

565
00:26:05,255 --> 00:26:06,957
I will do my best!

566
00:26:06,957 --> 00:26:08,959
Here goes.

567
00:26:08,959 --> 00:26:10,561
Question number 10!

568
00:26:13,464 --> 00:26:16,166
Conan Doyle brings to mind Sherlock Holmes,

569
00:26:16,166 --> 00:26:19,036
Masashi Yokomizo brings to mind Kousuke Kindaiji.

570
00:26:19,036 --> 00:26:21,238
Then what does Ranpo Edogawa bring to mind?

571
00:26:23,841 --> 00:26:26,143
-She did it! -Yes, Ms. Okino.

572
00:26:30,147 --> 00:26:32,750
Akechi, Akechi!

573
00:26:32,750 --> 00:26:34,952
Too bad, Ms. Okino, you're disqualified.

574
00:26:34,952 --> 00:26:37,855
The top prize winners are Ms. Kazuka Inoue and Ms. Azusa Yamamoto!

575
00:26:37,855 --> 00:26:39,456
Let's give them a bit hand!

576
00:26:39,456 --> 00:26:42,259
-Congratulations! -Congratulations for both winner.

577
00:26:42,259 --> 00:26:43,460
Oh boy.

578
00:26:43,460 --> 00:26:46,263
How could she say such a name?

579
00:26:46,263 --> 00:26:48,766
Kogoro Mouri!

580
00:26:49,867 --> 00:26:51,935
How disappointing.

581
00:27:39,817 --> 00:27:41,618
Next Conan's Hint:

582
00:27:41,618 --> 00:27:44,321
"Roma letters".

583
00:27:44,321 --> 00:27:45,823
The next episode involves a spider house.

584
00:27:45,823 --> 00:27:46,924
Are there going to be that many spies?

585
00:27:46,924 --> 00:27:49,026
He's talking about the insect!

